Adapted areas inside LOOMIER
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

The following LOOMIER files were inspired by — or derive concepts from — the
referenced OpenGame source files. None of the OpenGame source files were
copied verbatim; instead, the *ideas* (data shapes, check categories,
diagnostic taxonomy) were re-implemented from scratch in CommonJS JavaScript
to fit LOOMIER's declarative GameDefinition runtime.

  prototype/backend/src/debugProtocol/types.js
    inspired by  agent-test/debug-skill/src/types.ts
    adaptations  Mapped FailureStage and FixType to LOOMIER's JSON-only
                 declarative model. Removed Phaser/TypeScript-specific shapes.

  prototype/backend/src/debugProtocol/validator.js
    inspired by  agent-test/debug-skill/src/validator.ts
    adaptations  Replaced filesystem + regex-on-source walkers with pure
                 in-memory checks against the validated GameDefinition object.
                 Replaced TS/Phaser checks (asset-pack.json, animations.json,
                 scene registration in main.ts) with LOOMIER analogues that
                 operate on the runtime schema's entities/scenes/behaviors.

  prototype/backend/src/debugProtocol/diagnostics.js
    inspired by  agent-test/debug-skill/src/debug-loop.ts (entry shape only)
    adaptations  Stripped the LLM-driven repair loop. Stage 1 only collects
                 and reports diagnostics deterministically.

  prototype/backend/src/debugProtocol/seed-protocol.json
    inspired by  agent-test/debug-skill/seed-protocol/protocol.json (format)
    adaptations  All entries are LOOMIER-native, keyed to LOOMIER diagnostic
                 codes. None of OpenGame's TS-specific entries were copied.

The original OpenGame Phaser code generator, debug runner (Algorithm 1 REPEAT
loop), repairer, recorder, and generalizer modules are NOT used. LOOMIER
follows a no-arbitrary-JS-execution model: only declarative JSON.
